{"000-section": {"000-title": "West Bengal Govt. to Bring Unorganized Workers under Samajik Suraksha Yojana"}, "001-section": {"000-title": "WB govt. to bring unorganized sector workers under Social Security Scheme, Samajik Suraksha Yojana (SSY) to provide assistance of Rs. 20,000 p.a for ailment, Rs. 60,000 for hospitalization & provident fund (PF) facility"}, "002-section": {"000-title": "WB Govt. to Bring Unorganized Workers under SSY", "001-normal": "The state Labour Department of West Bengal is already undertaking a massive awareness campaign in order to bring more unorganized sector workers under the ambit of Samajik Suraksha Yojana. WB govt. has allocated Rs. 113 crore for the Social Security Scheme in seven years duration. The state govt. had previously merged 5 schemes into one scheme in the month of April of FY 2017 and had named the scheme as Samajik Suraksha Yojana (SSY).", "002-normal": "Under this SSY scheme, all the workers in unorganized sector are getting a financial assistance of Rs. 20,000 per annum for any ailment. These workers are liable to get upto Rs. 60,000 per annum in case of hospitalization. Moreover, there is also an entitlement for PF after the worker attains the age of 60 years.", "003-normal": "Till date, more than 1 crore people have been brought under the ambit of Samajik Suraksha Yojana. The state govt. is going to setup enrollment camps at the labour fair which is taking place in various districts of the state across the month of January 2019. The official website for Samajik Suraksha Yojana is https://www.ssy.wblabour.gov.in/", "004-normal": "The state government of West Bengal has also released a sum of Rs. 1600 crore to provide minimum support price (MSP) to a large number of farmers. As per the target, WB govt. had to procure 50 lakh tonnes of paddy till September 2018 but the govt. has expressed its desire to buy max. amount of paddy by February 2019.", "005-normal": "So, the state govt. has released a sum of Rs. 1600 crore for this purpose. The govt. will issue account payee cheques to the farmers on the spot whenever the farmers visits a procurement centre to sell their produce."}}